# Deny-by-default: nothing new at the repo root is tracked until it's
# explicitly whitelisted below. Inside a whitelisted folder, new files
# and subfolders are tracked normally — so dropping a new logo into
# primary-logo/ or adding a new department just works.

/*

# Whitelisted top-level entries
!/.gitignore
!/LICENSE
!/README.md
!/brand-guide/
!/departments/
!/dist/
!/favicon/
!/initiatives/
!/primary-logo/
!/primary-logo-with-address/
!/web-tokens/

# OS / editor junk at any depth
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/desktop.ini
**/~$*
**/*.tmp
